"MDc6TGljZW5zZTU="},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":false,"topics":["deep-learning","keras","numpy","pytorch","scattering-transform","scikit-learn","tensorflow","wavelets"],"visibility":"public","forks":112,"open_issues":69,"watchers":617,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"body":"While rebasing PR #871 i noticed that our `concatenate` operator has strange default values for `dims`:\r\n\r\n\r\nHere's `backend/numpy_backend.py`:\r\n```python\r\n    @classmethod\r\n    def concatenate(cls, arrays, dim=1):\r\n        return cls._np.stack(arrays, axis=dim)\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere's `backend/tensorflow_backend.py`:\r\n```python\r\n    @staticmethod\r\n    def concatenate(arrays, dim=1):\r\n        return tf.stack(arrays, axis=dim)\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere's `backend/torch_backend.py`:\r\n```python\r\n   @staticmethod\r\n    def concatenate(arrays, dim=2):\r\n        return torch.stack(arrays, dim=dim)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm a bit confused by this `dim=2` default value. And not too happy that the kwargs is called `dim` instead of `axis`, which would be more compliant with the Python Array API. \r\n\r\nOur decision here will affect the semantics of #902 \r\n\r\n@eickenberg  thoughts?","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kymatio/kymatio/issues/903/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kymatio/kymatio/issues/903/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"id":6949896616,"node_id":"LE_lADOCQLq_c5NQqBAzwAAAAGePwGo","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kymatio/kymatio/issues/events/6949896616","actor":{"login":"lostanlen","id":3943142,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM5NDMxNDI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3943142?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lostanlen","html_url":"