nloads":true,"has_wiki":false,"has_pages":false,"has_discussions":true,"forks_count":112,"mirror_url":null,"archived":false,"disabled":false,"open_issues_count":69,"license":{"key":"bsd-3-clause","name":"BSD 3-Clause \"New\" or \"Revised\" License","spdx_id":"BSD-3-Clause","url":"https://api.github.com/licenses/bsd-3-clause","node_id":"MDc6TGljZW5zZTU="},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":false,"topics":["deep-learning","keras","numpy","pytorch","scattering-transform","scikit-learn","tensorflow","wavelets"],"visibility":"public","forks":112,"open_issues":69,"watchers":617,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kymatio/kymatio/pulls/919","html_url":"https://github.com/kymatio/kymatio/pull/919","diff_url":"https://github.com/kymatio/kymatio/pull/919.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/kymatio/kymatio/pull/919.patch","merged_at":"2022-08-14T14:38:50Z"},"body":"and remove deprecated `average` kwarg\r\n\r\nCloses #902 \r\n\r\nRationale:\r\n\r\n> Now that we have a `T` parameter (#673) and that `average` is deprecated (#884), i think it's time we consider passing `T='global'` to the constructor so that it skips the `phi` and performs a 1D uniform average, also known as \"global average pooling\", instead. This will be faster (`O(N)` instead of `O(N log N)`) and conceptually simpler than the default `T=None` (i.e., `2**J`).\r\n\r\nNote that this implementation does _not_ introduce new keyword arguments to the Scattering1D constructor. Rather, it special-cases a new string value for `T`: `'global'`. This is backwards compatible. Local averaging `T=2**J` remains and will remain the default.\r\n\r\nTo implement this, i have added a new Kymatio primitive, namely `sum`:\r\n\r\n`def sum(x, axis)`\r\nwhere `axis` is an `int` (for 1D) or `tuple` of `int`'s (for 2D/3D)\r\n\r\nThanks to the new generator of core implementation (#880), i am able to skip unpadding when performing global averaging. So this should be faster and memory-efficient, although i haven't formally tested it in practice.\r\n\r\nI have modified the internal values of `average` and the prototype of `core`, but this isn't anything the user accesses directly, so i guess it's fine to break things.\r\n(in fact we've been warning the user against accessing average for several months now. and core is now wrapped inside a unified frontend #908 so i don't see why users would call it directly)\r\n\r\nI have added a simple NumPy test, feel free to request more if you have ideas or specific use cases.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kymatio/kymatio/issues/919/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kymatio/kymatio/issues/919/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"id":7184790066,"node_id":"CE_lADOCQLq_c5NQqBAzwAAAAGsPzIy","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kymatio/kymatio/issues/events/7184790066","actor":{"login":"cyrusvahidi","id":10761938,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwNzYxOTM4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10761938?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/cyrusvahidi","html_url":"https://github.com/cyrusvahidi","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cyrusvahidi/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cyrusvahidi/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cyrusvahidi/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cyrusvahidi/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cyrusvahidi/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cyrusvahidi/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cyrusvahidi/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cyrusvahidi/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"http